This paper involves the use of machine learning models for crime prediction, which falls under the category of computational criminology. The use of geospatial features and reverse geocoding techniques suggests a focus on spatial analysis, which is commonly found in the sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). However, the paper's emphasis on machine learning and data analysis suggests that it is more likely to belong to the sub-categories of cybersecurity (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), or graphics (cs.GR).
